name: Coconut Curry Greens with Runny Eggs

steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Trim and rinse the spinach
- Center ribs and remove stems from the Tuscan kale
- Remove the outer layers from the lemon grass
- Coarsely chop the ginger
- Coarsely chop the garlic
- Tear the basil

### Steps
1. Slice 1 chile into rings, flicking out seeds and removing membranes if desired
2. Transfer to a medium bowl. Add 1 tsp. sugar, 1 Tbsp. lime juice (from ½ lime), and a pinch of salt and toss to combine; set aside until ready to use
3. Cut remaining lime half into wedges; set aside for serving
4. Coarsely chop remaining chile.
5. Cook spinach and kale in a large pot of boiling salted water until bright green and tender, 1–2 minutes
6. Immediately transfer to an ice bath
7. Drain and squeeze dry (no need to squeeze to death), then coarsely chop
8. Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in a 10" skillet over medium until shimmering.
9. Cook coriander seeds, stirring frequently, until fragrant and a shade darker, 2–3 minutes
10. Reduce heat to medium-low and add chopped chile, lemongrass, ginger, garlic, and curry leaves (if using); season with salt
11. Cook, stirring frequently, until curry leaves are crisp and aromatics are just starting to soften, about 3 minutes
12. Transfer lemongrass mixture to a blender or food processor and blend until finely chopped
13. Add coconut milk, 1 cup cilantro, 1 cup basil, ¾ tsp. salt, and remaining 1½ Tbsp. lime juice and 1 tsp. sugar
14. Continue to blend until smooth. Taste and season with salt if needed
15. Heat same skillet over medium (no need to wipe out)
16. Add greens and cook, stirring to gently separate and cook off remaining liquid, 1–2 minutes
17. Pour curry sauce over, stir to combine, and bring to a very gentle simmer
18. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is thickened and greens are very tender, 4–6 minutes. Season with salt.
19. Using a spoon, make 6 indentations in greens, then crack an egg into each
20. Cover and cook, rotating pan occasionally, until egg whites are opaque and cooked through, 6–10 minutes, depending on how runny you want them
21. Remove from heat and sit 5 minutes to give sauce a chance to set.
22. Right before serving, add remaining ½ cup cilantro and ¼ cup basil to reserved chile-lime mixture
23. Season with salt and gently toss to combine
24. Top shakshuka with herb salad and drizzle with oil. Serve with reserved lime wedges and rice alongside (if using).

ingredients.note: Or any other hot chile such as Holland or Thai
